@ClemMakesApps Thanks Clement for the details!
We also have an internal discussion. And the conclusion is, we are going to use the npm release version on zrender in echarts project, for both master and release branch. And if there's a breaking change in zrender that echarts relies on, we will publish a non-latest version of zrender first, and then merge the related logic of echarts from a feature branch into master or release branch.
Besides, I'm working on a full doc for developing workflow so that people from the community can understand how to help.

Thanks for your contribution!

